1
00:02:39,221 --> 00:02:40,806
All right, Earl.

2
00:02:46,728 --> 00:02:48,689
Next. Come on, step right through.

3
00:02:48,772 --> 00:02:51,775
Sir, I need you to take your belt off
and go back through.

4
00:02:53,819 --> 00:02:55,195
-Good, Mick.
-Hello.

5
00:02:55,278 --> 00:02:57,739
Mick! Mick, I was just calling you.

6
00:02:57,823 --> 00:03:00,158
Hey, I was just calling you at the office.
I gotta talk to you.

7
00:03:00,242 --> 00:03:02,744
-Come on, stick with me.
-How long are you gonna be here today?

8
00:03:02,828 --> 00:03:04,830
Depends on when the judge calls my client.

9
00:03:04,913 --> 00:03:07,749
See, what does it say about me
that I let you treat me like this, huh?

10
00:03:07,833 --> 00:03:10,502
I'm giving you a big chance
to move up in the world and help me.

11
00:03:10,585 --> 00:03:12,879
-My daughter's about to go to surgery.
-I've heard it all before, Val.

12
00:03:12,963 --> 00:03:14,089
Come on, baby, talk to me.
What do you got?

13
00:03:14,172 --> 00:03:16,508
Okay, I got something big for you.
This guy's gonna be the big money.

14
00:03:16,591 --> 00:03:17,592
It's in Inglewood.

15
00:03:17,676 --> 00:03:20,762
But the problem is that he goes up
before the judge at noon, okay?

16
00:03:20,846 --> 00:03:22,097
-You listening to me?
-I'm listening.

17
00:03:22,180 --> 00:03:23,849
So the client,
his mother and his mother's lawyer

18
00:03:23,932 --> 00:03:25,767
comes to my office at 8:00 a.m.
in the morning...

19
00:03:25,851 --> 00:03:28,395
-He's already got a lawyer?
-Just listen.

20
00:03:28,478 --> 00:03:30,981
Listen, it's not criminal,
it's just real estate, okay?

21
00:03:31,064 --> 00:03:32,816
And I made them so crazy about you

22
00:03:32,899 --> 00:03:35,610
that now they want to put up
their Malibu beach house against a million.

23
00:03:35,694 --> 00:03:37,362
-The bail's a million?
-Yeah.

24
00:03:37,446 --> 00:03:39,865
-What did they book this guy for?
-I say it's a romantic tiff.

25
00:03:39,948 --> 00:03:41,533
The cops are saying
he beat up the girl really bad.

26
00:03:41,616 --> 00:03:44,035
They want assault with a deadly weapon,
throw in a GBI.

27
00:03:44,119 --> 00:03:45,620
-Has the DA filed yet?
-Yes, he did.

28
00:03:45,704 --> 00:03:48,039
See, I take care of my friends.
I even take care of you, bubba.

29
00:03:48,290 --> 00:03:49,624
Inglewood by noon.

30
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:51,251
You could do it, man.
Go through some red lights,

31
00:03:51,334 --> 00:03:53,420
-break the speed limit.
-Be honest with me, Val. Is this real?

32
00:03:53,503 --> 00:03:54,796
Don't bullshit me. Is this gonna stick?

33
00:03:54,880 --> 00:03:57,591
Of course it is. Would I lie to you?
And you're gonna take care of me, right?

34
00:03:57,674 --> 00:04:01,303
Make them forget the beach house
and go for my bond.

35
00:04:01,386 --> 00:04:04,222
-What's his name?
-Louis. Louis Roulet.

36
00:04:04,306 --> 00:04:07,267
R-O-U-L-E-T, like the wheel.

37
00:04:07,517 --> 00:04:10,604
That's not how you spell the wheel,
but got it.

38
00:04:14,316 --> 00:04:17,611
Roberto!

39
00:04:17,694 --> 00:04:21,323
Do you mind checking that list,
seeing where my man Harold Casey is on it?

40
00:04:24,201 --> 00:04:25,243
Don't go that low.

41
00:04:25,327 --> 00:04:28,413
I got a case across town at noon
I gotta get to.

42
00:04:28,497 --> 00:04:30,749
Do you mind just bringing him down?
I'll only be a second.

43
00:04:30,832 --> 00:04:32,000
-Reynaldo.
-Pardon me?

44
00:04:33,835 --> 00:04:38,840
My name's Reynaldo, not Roberto.
Us bailiffs all look alike, right?

45
00:04:39,132 --> 00:04:41,426
-Your man white?
-Yeah, he's white.

46
00:04:41,510 --> 00:04:45,764
- I got blacks down here right now.
-All right, listen, Reynaldo.

47
00:04:45,847 --> 00:04:48,642
My bad on your name.
I took a wild-ass guess. I was wrong.

48
00:04:48,725 --> 00:04:51,061
But I didn't forget you at Christmastime,
did 1?

49
00:04:51,144 --> 00:04:53,313
Remember that jar of nuts
with the prize inside?

50
00:04:53,396 --> 00:04:55,607
"Happy holidays. Your friend, Mick."

51
00:04:55,690 --> 00:04:59,319
-I went through those pretty fast.
-All right, let's make it two this time.

52
00:04:59,861 --> 00:05:02,531
Okay. I'll bring your body down,
but you better make it quick.

53
00:05:02,614 --> 00:05:04,449
Gracias, Reynaldo.

54
00:05:04,533 --> 00:05:06,618
Harold Casey. Yeah, bring him down.

55
00:05:08,495 --> 00:05:12,958
Harold. You shouldn't be running
from your lawyer. It's bad form.

56
00:05:13,124 --> 00:05:14,793
Now, you know what I want to talk about.

57
00:05:14,876 --> 00:05:16,962
In a minute,
Judge Powell's gonna call us down.

58
00:05:17,045 --> 00:05:18,922
He's gonna want to know
if we're ready for trial.

59
00:05:19,005 --> 00:05:21,216
-We are.
-We are not. And you know why not.

60
00:05:21,424 --> 00:05:24,219
Rule one, I get paid or I don't work.

61
00:05:24,302 --> 00:05:28,223
-Don't worry, I got your money.
-Exactly. You got it, I don't.

62
00:05:28,431 --> 00:05:30,350
It's coming. I talked to my boys.

63
00:05:30,433 --> 00:05:34,479
Listen, Harold, I looked on the list
of people I trust. You're not on it.

64
00:05:34,563 --> 00:05:40,193
The law says you can't just quit.
The judge won't let you. I looked it up.

65
00:05:40,277 --> 00:05:43,113
Pay close attention.

66
00:05:43,196 --> 00:05:47,409
Michael Haller for the defense, Your Honor.
If I may, I'd like to carry this over.

67
00:05:47,492 --> 00:05:48,869
Do you have a reason, Mr. Haller?

68
00:05:48,952 --> 00:05:52,497
I'm having trouble locating a witness,
Your Honor, an indispensable witness.

69
00:05:52,581 --> 00:05:53,748
A Mr. Green?

70
00:05:54,416 --> 00:05:57,919
-How much time do you need?
-That's hard to say.

71
00:05:58,003 --> 00:06:00,755
-Does the state object?
-No, Your Honor.

72
00:06:00,839 --> 00:06:06,177
All right, I'm gonna hold this over
pending notification from counsel.

73
00:06:06,636 --> 00:06:11,600
-That was some bullshit, man.
-Yeah. I expect to hear from you, Harold.

74
00:06:20,942 --> 00:06:24,112
Inglewood, Earl.
Keep it on the surface streets.

75
00:06:41,129 --> 00:06:43,882
Earl, headphones.

76
00:06:43,965 --> 00:06:46,843
-This is Haller.
-And this is your office.

77
00:06:46,968 --> 00:06:50,889
Actually, I'm in my office, Miss Lorna,
on my way to the courthouse in Inglewood.

78
00:06:51,056 --> 00:06:53,725
Listen, jot down
to remind me to give Reynaldo,

79
00:06:53,808 --> 00:06:56,811
the bailiff over in San Fernando,
200 bucks for Christmas, all right?

80
00:06:56,937 --> 00:06:59,731
Got it.
Hey, did Val reach you about his customer?

81
00:06:59,814 --> 00:07:03,985
Yeah. "I got something big for you, Mick."
Every time. Any other calls?

82
00:07:04,069 --> 00:07:05,904
No, just some odds and ends.

83
00:07:06,071 --> 00:07:08,323
A few DUlls.
I just quoted them the house number.

84
00:07:08,490 --> 00:07:11,534
-Gloria Larson called from county lockup.
-She got popped again?

85
00:07:11,618 --> 00:07:14,120
The usual with a complication,
cocaine possession.

86
00:07:14,245 --> 00:07:18,500
-Her first appearance is right after lunch.
-Look, tell her I'll try.

87
00:07:22,420 --> 00:07:25,548
So, I was thinking, boss, you know,
when you get your license back or whatnot,

88
00:07:25,632 --> 00:07:31,054
maybe I can stay on, like,
a permanent thing or something, you know?

89
00:07:31,137 --> 00:07:34,057
I got my license back
three months ago, Earl.

90
00:07:43,483 --> 00:07:47,278
Hey, boss. Do you want me
to do something about that? 'Cause I can.

91
00:07:47,779 --> 00:07:50,699
No, just keep doing what you're doing.

92
00:08:01,376 --> 00:08:02,794
Boss.

93
00:08:04,045 --> 00:08:06,089
All right. Pull over up here.

94
00:08:24,065 --> 00:08:25,692
-Counselor.
-Eddie.

95
00:08:25,775 --> 00:08:29,404
-How's it hanging?
-A little to the left, my man. How about you?

96
00:08:29,904 --> 00:08:31,322
Not bad.

97
00:08:31,489 --> 00:08:33,033
Your ride's a little messy.

98
00:08:33,116 --> 00:08:37,579
Yeah, the maid doesn't come till Tuesday.
What can I do for you, big man?

99
00:08:37,662 --> 00:08:39,330
Our boy Harold called from the pen,

100
00:08:39,414 --> 00:08:42,000
said you're stalling his case
till you see some more green.

101
00:08:42,083 --> 00:08:45,920
- I don't get paid, I don't work.
-We paid you. $5,000.

102
00:08:46,004 --> 00:08:47,380
That's long gone, Eddie.

103
00:08:47,464 --> 00:08:50,884
Look, I could tell you that half of it
went to an aerial-photo expert.

104
00:08:50,967 --> 00:08:53,845
He's gonna blow the state's case
by showing that the DEA

105
00:08:53,928 --> 00:08:57,599
violated the airspace over Harold's farm
by flying too low.

106
00:08:57,932 --> 00:09:01,978
I could also tell you that I gotta fly that guy
in from New York City, get him to testify,

107
00:09:02,062 --> 00:09:03,980
put him up in a hotel
and all that kind of stuff,

108
00:09:04,064 --> 00:09:09,110
but you don't need to know that.
All you need to know is that we had a deal.

109
00:09:09,194 --> 00:09:11,029
It's time to refill the tank.

110
00:09:11,112 --> 00:09:14,699
-What, another five grand?
-Ten.

111
00:09:14,783 --> 00:09:17,368
He wants to fly business,
wants a first-class hotel.

112
00:09:17,452 --> 00:09:19,537
And we want Harold back on the farm.

113
00:09:19,788 --> 00:09:21,706
He's our best farmer,
if you know what I mean.

114
00:09:21,790 --> 00:09:24,584
I don't, and I don't want to.

115
00:09:24,667 --> 00:09:28,880
Now, look, either pay me
or go with a public defender.

116
00:09:28,963 --> 00:09:30,965
He won't know much about airspace, but...

117
00:09:40,517 --> 00:09:43,603
-Ain't you gonna count it?
- I just did.

118
00:09:43,895 --> 00:09:46,481
Keep that rubber on the road, Eddie.

119
00:09:47,649 --> 00:09:49,984
Let's roll, Earl.

120
00:09:52,987 --> 00:09:54,531
So, this expert flying in from New York,

121
00:09:54,614 --> 00:09:56,116
do you want me
to pick him up at the airport?

122
00:09:56,199 --> 00:09:59,160
-There's nobody coming in.
-What?

123
00:09:59,244 --> 00:10:04,749
The best camera experts in the world
are right here in Hollywood.

124
00:10:04,833 --> 00:10:06,084
Nice.

125
00:10:06,167 --> 00:10:09,921
You know what?
You would've done all right on the streets.

126
00:10:10,004 --> 00:10:12,841
Shit. Where do you think I am, Earl?

127
00:10:36,406 --> 00:10:38,533
-Louis Roulet?
-Yes.

128
00:10:40,702 --> 00:10:42,120
I'm Michael Haller.

129
00:10:42,203 --> 00:10:45,039
Mr. Haller, I called you
because I need someone.

130
00:10:45,290 --> 00:10:46,541
This whole thing is a setup.

131
00:10:46,624 --> 00:10:48,793
I made a mistake with that woman,
and she was setting me up.

132
00:10:48,877 --> 00:10:50,795
Keep your voice down. Hear me?

133
00:10:50,879 --> 00:10:54,549
Don't say anything about the case
until I get you out on bail.

134
00:10:55,717 --> 00:11:00,847
-I understand your family lawyer's in court.
-Yes. His name's Cecil Dobbs.

135
00:11:00,930 --> 00:11:02,056
He's here somewhere.

136
00:11:02,140 --> 00:11:06,519
I'll find him.
Tell me about yourself. How old are you?

137
00:11:06,603 --> 00:11:07,687
Thirty-two.

138
00:11:07,770 --> 00:11:10,356
Ties to the community?
Did you grow up here?

139
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:14,861
Yeah, Beverly Hills. I went to USC.
I work for my mother's business.

140
00:11:15,069 --> 00:11:17,739
-How about your father?
-He died when I was two.

141
00:11:19,824 --> 00:11:24,204
-How much did you make last year, Louis?
-My taxes said $600,000.

142
00:11:24,287 --> 00:11:28,666
I want a lawyer, too. My name's Corliss,
two "S's". Do you got a card on you?

143
00:11:28,750 --> 00:11:31,252
Listen, buddy,
they'll have a lawyer for you out there.

144
00:11:31,336 --> 00:11:34,255
Right now I need you to back away
and give us a little space.

145
00:11:36,925 --> 00:11:39,093
Can you do that, pal?

146
00:11:39,260 --> 00:11:41,346
-I'm backing, boss.
-There we go.

147
00:11:41,429 --> 00:11:43,097
Okay.

148
00:11:43,431 --> 00:11:45,600
There we go. There we go.

149
00:11:46,100 --> 00:11:49,687
Listen, they've put some
heavy charges on you, Louis.

150
00:11:49,771 --> 00:11:51,856
The DA's probably going to ask for no bail.

151
00:11:51,940 --> 00:11:55,485
-Wait, no bail?
-I said they're gonna ask for it.

152
00:11:55,568 --> 00:11:57,195
When was the last time you were arrested?

153
00:11:57,278 --> 00:11:58,363
Never.

154
00:11:58,446 --> 00:12:02,033
-So, if I checked your record...
-You'd find parking tickets.

155
00:12:02,492 --> 00:12:04,369
Are you gonna get me out of here?

156
00:12:04,452 --> 00:12:06,454
I'm gonna try, Louis.

157
00:12:13,461 --> 00:12:17,840
Are you the prosecutor
who used to have the Roulet case?

158
00:12:17,924 --> 00:12:22,345
-Haller! Son of a bitch.
-Rules are rules.

159
00:12:22,679 --> 00:12:26,474
I wanted this one. Okay, okay, I'll go quietly.

160
00:12:27,558 --> 00:12:30,228
But after today's hearing,
if you don't object.

161
00:12:30,395 --> 00:12:35,942
-It depends. Are you going for no bail?
-That won't change with the prosecutor.

162
00:12:36,025 --> 00:12:38,152
Not after what your guy did.

163
00:12:38,278 --> 00:12:40,780
-If he did it.
-Sure, if.

164
00:12:40,863 --> 00:12:44,242
They only picked him up in her home
with blood all over him.

165
00:12:44,325 --> 00:12:46,327
I love it when you get sarcastic.

166
00:12:47,996 --> 00:12:50,456
Can I at least see the arrest report?

167
00:12:50,540 --> 00:12:53,918
You get it from whomever takes over.
No favors on this one.

168
00:12:56,504 --> 00:12:57,797
How's Hayley today?

169
00:13:00,174 --> 00:13:03,303
-She's good.
-Good.

170
00:13:03,386 --> 00:13:06,097
I'll pick her up the usual time on Saturday.

171
00:13:06,180 --> 00:13:10,518
Because of the seriousness of the offense,
the financial resources of the accused,

172
00:13:10,768 --> 00:13:12,228
the state requests no bail.

173
00:13:12,312 --> 00:13:16,399
Your Honor, there's no way the state can
claim that my client is a flight risk. He's not.

174
00:13:16,482 --> 00:13:19,610
With resources like this man has,
flight is always a risk.

175
00:13:19,694 --> 00:13:21,487
-Are there any priors?
-No, Your Honor.

176
00:13:21,571 --> 00:13:25,950
Then I'm going to reduce the risk of flight
by ordering him to wear a tracer anklet

177
00:13:26,034 --> 00:13:28,077
and I'm going to set bail at $1 million.

178
00:13:28,369 --> 00:13:31,581
-Judge, have you seen the photo?
-Miss McPherson, bail is set.

179
00:13:31,789 --> 00:13:33,416
Thank you, Judge.

180
00:13:35,209 --> 00:13:38,254
Mick. Feeling compelled to thank me
and speak well of me,

181
00:13:38,338 --> 00:13:39,881
'cause this one's gonna be the money,
I'm telling you.

182
00:13:39,964 --> 00:13:43,509
-We'll see, we'll see.
-There's his lawyer right there. Cecil Dobbs.

183
00:13:43,593 --> 00:13:45,970
Hey, Mick, don't forget our deal.

184
00:13:46,054 --> 00:13:49,640
A possibility, but...
He's here now. I'll talk to you later.

185
00:13:49,724 --> 00:13:52,602
-Cecil Dobbs.
-Mr. Haller.

186
00:13:54,187 --> 00:13:57,231
It's depressing to see the boy
caught up in that cattle call.

187
00:13:57,315 --> 00:13:59,525
The boy?

188
00:13:59,609 --> 00:14:01,986
I've represented the family for a long time.

189
00:14:02,236 --> 00:14:05,239
Listen, my advice is,
let Val fix you up with a bond.

190
00:14:05,323 --> 00:14:07,158
Then you take the boy home.

191
00:14:07,241 --> 00:14:10,578
But we were thinking of putting up property,
Mrs. Windsor's beach house.

192
00:14:10,912 --> 00:14:12,080
The mother's name is Windsor?

193
00:14:12,163 --> 00:14:14,499
Her second husband's name.
He's dead now.

194
00:14:14,791 --> 00:14:16,626
Assessing the house will take days.

195
00:14:16,709 --> 00:14:19,504
Trust me, you don't want the boy in the clink
for even that long.

196
00:14:19,587 --> 00:14:23,508
So tap Val, take Louis to your office.
I'll meet you there at 4:00.

197
00:14:24,008 --> 00:14:27,929
Here, let me give you my business card.

198
00:14:28,554 --> 00:14:30,765
Oh, boy.

199
00:14:31,015 --> 00:14:34,852
Media? Yeah, they're already on us.

200
00:14:34,936 --> 00:14:38,314
Mrs. Windsor is sensitive about the press,

201
00:14:38,398 --> 00:14:41,692
but I guess there's not much
we can do about that.

202
00:14:41,776 --> 00:14:45,863
Let me see. Say, bub, come here. Come here.

203
00:14:46,697 --> 00:14:48,616
I saw you filming in there.
What's your name?

204
00:14:48,741 --> 00:14:52,578
-The name's Rob Gillon. They call me Sticks.
-Sticks, you freelancing on this?

205
00:14:52,662 --> 00:14:55,248
Yeah, your client's got profile.
I figure I'd sell it to local news.

206
00:14:55,331 --> 00:14:56,916
-How much?
-How much what?

207
00:14:56,999 --> 00:14:58,960
How much they pay you
for what you shot in there?

208
00:14:59,043 --> 00:15:01,838
That depends. $700, $750.

209
00:15:01,921 --> 00:15:05,758
Yeah? How about we take
it off your hands for $8007?

210
00:15:06,676 --> 00:15:08,970
No? Too short?

211
00:15:09,345 --> 00:15:12,473
-All right, let's make it a grand. Deal?
-It's yours.

212
00:15:12,557 --> 00:15:13,641
Sold.

213
00:15:14,267 --> 00:15:17,687
-I can expense this, right?
-Of course. Absolutely.

214
00:15:17,770 --> 00:15:20,148
-Thank you, Sticks.
-Thank you.

215
00:15:21,691 --> 00:15:23,860
You know, Mr. Haller,
you weren't my choice.

216
00:15:24,152 --> 00:15:27,613
I'll bet I wasn't. A firm like yours
must have some heavy hitters on call.

217
00:15:27,697 --> 00:15:29,782
We do. But Louis insisted.

218
00:15:31,242 --> 00:15:35,955
Frankly, I've never heard of you,
but maybe I should have.

219
00:15:36,038 --> 00:15:40,668
-Did you say I was Louis' choice?
-Yes. He'd read about a case you handled.

220
00:15:43,671 --> 00:15:48,050
I'll need 100 grand up front, working off
$550 an hour. Another 100 if we go to trial,

221
00:15:48,134 --> 00:15:51,679
more if we go past a week.
Appeals, we start over.

222
00:15:55,683 --> 00:15:58,102
I take it none of that's a problem.

223
00:15:58,186 --> 00:16:00,313
-No.
-See you at 4:00.

224
00:16:14,368 --> 00:16:18,456
-Where we headed now?
