1124
01:23:36,281 --> 01:23:39,451
-What happened next?
-Something hit me from behind.

1125
01:23:39,535 --> 01:23:43,080
I blacked out. I have no idea for how long.

1126
01:23:43,163 --> 01:23:44,456
Is that all?

1127
01:23:44,540 --> 01:23:47,376
When I woke up,
two guys were sitting on me,

1128
01:23:47,918 --> 01:23:53,090
telling me not to move.
I couldn't anyway. I was scared.

1129
01:23:54,132 --> 01:23:57,803
But you had blood on your sweater.
And on your left hand.

1130
01:23:58,136 --> 01:24:00,180
Someone put it there because I didn't.

1131
01:24:00,264 --> 01:24:02,516
You didn't strike Miss Campo
with your left fist?

1132
01:24:02,599 --> 01:24:05,018
-No.
-Threaten to rape her? Threaten to kill her?

1133
01:24:05,102 --> 01:24:06,979
No, I am not that guy!

1134
01:24:08,939 --> 01:24:12,859
Do you have any idea what it's like
to be accused of something like this?

1135
01:24:12,943 --> 01:24:16,572
To sit there and listen to people
tell lies about you,

1136
01:24:16,655 --> 01:24:20,659
about your having done something
this sick and depraved,

1137
01:24:20,742 --> 01:24:25,205
call you an animal, talk about your sex life,
humiliate you?

1138
01:24:25,789 --> 01:24:27,457
Listen, I understand the process.

1139
01:24:27,541 --> 01:24:31,837
I know I had to sit there
and be quiet and wait my chance,

1140
01:24:31,920 --> 01:24:37,092
but if guilty people have rights,
then what about innocent people?

1141
01:24:37,342 --> 01:24:38,844
I am innocent!

1142
01:24:41,763 --> 01:24:45,017
I'm innocent and I want this behind me!

1143
01:24:46,685 --> 01:24:49,688
I have no further questions, Your Honor.

1144
01:24:49,771 --> 01:24:55,569
According to you,
Miss Campo punched herself,

1145
01:24:55,694 --> 01:24:58,155
or she had someone she had never met

1146
01:24:58,572 --> 01:25:02,534
violently and viciously beat her
as a part of a setup?

1147
01:25:02,618 --> 01:25:07,497
-All I know is that I didn't.
-And this knife that you always carry.

1148
01:25:07,831 --> 01:25:10,042
How did she know she'd find it on you
as part of the setup?

1149
01:25:10,125 --> 01:25:15,255
I guess she couldn't, could she?
I never take it out, I never show it to anyone,

1150
01:25:15,339 --> 01:25:19,259
so she must have just found it
in my pocket after she,

1151
01:25:19,343 --> 01:25:22,179
or whoever, knocked me out.
Isn't that right?

1152
01:25:22,346 --> 01:25:26,141
- Would prefer if I asked the questions.
-Okay.

1153
01:25:27,517 --> 01:25:32,898
Mr. Roulet, I'd like you to take a...
Take a look at this photo.

1154
01:25:32,981 --> 01:25:33,982
Tell me again.

1155
01:25:34,691 --> 01:25:40,530
Do you think Regina Campo would or could
have done this to herself?

1156
01:25:41,573 --> 01:25:46,662
I don't know who did it, but it wasn't me.
Nobody deserves that to happen.

1157
01:25:46,745 --> 01:25:49,331
What do you mean by "deserves"?

1158
01:25:51,249 --> 01:25:54,086
Do you mean crimes of violence

1159
01:25:54,169 --> 01:25:57,506
only come down to a woman
getting what she deserves?

1160
01:25:57,589 --> 01:26:01,259
I mean, no matter what she does,
or who she is,

1161
01:26:02,678 --> 01:26:04,513
no woman deserves that.

1162
01:26:06,431 --> 01:26:09,267
I have nothing further, Your Honor.

1163
01:26:10,143 --> 01:26:14,106
-Mr. Roulet, you are excused.
-Thank you.

1164
01:26:15,107 --> 01:26:17,567
The defense rests, Your Honor.

1165
01:26:31,581 --> 01:26:34,918
Before deciding to rest its case, the state
would like to take the night, Your Honor.

1166
01:26:35,502 --> 01:26:38,922
-For what purpose?
-To consider a rebuttal witness.

1167
01:26:40,382 --> 01:26:43,927
-What witness is he talking about?
-I have no idea.

1168
01:26:44,761 --> 01:26:49,266
The court will adjourn until 10:00 tomorrow.

1169
01:27:07,784 --> 01:27:09,453
-Morning, Bill.
-Morning.

1170
01:27:09,619 --> 01:27:11,580
I want to go grab some coffee.
You want some?

1171
01:27:11,663 --> 01:27:15,083
-No, man. I'm off caffeine.
-Right. Say, is that the custody list?

1172
01:27:15,167 --> 01:27:16,168
Yeah.

1173
01:27:16,251 --> 01:27:18,086
Let me see if any of my no-good clients
are on there.

1174
01:27:18,170 --> 01:27:19,296
Sure.

1175
01:27:25,051 --> 01:27:27,012
Lorna.

1176
01:27:27,095 --> 01:27:29,890
Okay, Minton's putting Corliss on.
He's already in lockup.

1177
01:27:29,973 --> 01:27:31,308
-That's great.
-Yeah, it's good.

1178
01:27:31,391 --> 01:27:33,185
How'd it go with you?
Did you serve Kurlen?

1179
01:27:33,393 --> 01:27:36,730
-Yes, I did.
-Okay. I'm going back to the courtroom.

1180
01:27:36,813 --> 01:27:37,898
Stand by.

1181
01:27:37,981 --> 01:27:39,232
Okay.

1182
01:27:41,818 --> 01:27:46,072
Hey, Haller, what is this bullshit?
I have nothing to do with this case.

1183
01:27:46,156 --> 01:27:49,075
"Subpoena to appear as a witness."

1184
01:27:49,159 --> 01:27:53,330
You'll just have to wait and see.
It's a legal document, Detective.

1185
01:28:10,972 --> 01:28:14,100
-Hey. Glad you made it.
-Working your magic?

1186
01:28:14,184 --> 01:28:17,854
- I got a little something up my sleeve.
-See you later.

1187
01:28:24,194 --> 01:28:26,947
Mr. Minton,
does the state have any rebuttal?

1188
01:28:29,866 --> 01:28:32,786
The state intends to call
Dwayne Jeffrey Corliss

1189
01:28:32,869 --> 01:28:34,162
as a rebuttal witness, Your Honor.

1190
01:28:34,246 --> 01:28:38,500
Judge, who is this witness?
And why wasn't I told about him until now?

1191
01:28:39,084 --> 01:28:40,836
Bailiff, remove the jury.

1192
01:28:48,051 --> 01:28:50,512
A fair question. Mr. Minton.

1193
01:28:50,595 --> 01:28:53,765
Dwayne Corliss is a cooperating witness
who spoke with Mr. Roulet

1194
01:28:53,849 --> 01:28:55,225
in custody following his arrest.

1195
01:28:55,308 --> 01:28:58,395
-That's a lie! I didn't speak to anyone!
-Be quiet, Mr. Roulet!

1196
01:28:58,603 --> 01:29:01,731
-Mr. Haller, control your client.
-Good. Let me take it from here.

1197
01:29:01,815 --> 01:29:04,568
Judge, I share my client's outrage.

1198
01:29:04,651 --> 01:29:07,487
And how long has the state
been sitting on this testimony?

1199
01:29:07,571 --> 01:29:09,364
Mr. Corliss just came forward yesterday,
Your Honor.

1200
01:29:09,447 --> 01:29:12,534
Yesterday? This is incredible.

1201
01:29:12,951 --> 01:29:16,454
Do you want to go back and talk to him?
Given the timing, I'd allow it.

1202
01:29:16,538 --> 01:29:20,083
No. Thank you, though, Judge.
I think we all know what this is.

1203
01:29:20,292 --> 01:29:23,003
Mr. Minton's putting a jailhouse snitch
on the stand,

1204
01:29:23,086 --> 01:29:24,713
and everything he says will be a lie.

1205
01:29:24,921 --> 01:29:28,341
-That's groundless, Your Honor.
- want my objection noted.

1206
01:29:28,425 --> 01:29:33,054
Then I'm going to rule. He can testify.
Call the jury in.

1207
01:29:33,388 --> 01:29:35,724
May I ask one indulgence, Your Honor?

1208
01:29:35,807 --> 01:29:38,602
May I step into the hallway
and make a call to an investigator

1209
01:29:38,727 --> 01:29:41,479
for whatever good it may do
at this late date?

1210
01:29:41,563 --> 01:29:43,857
Thank you, Your Honor.

1211
01:29:51,281 --> 01:29:52,616
Yep, I'm here.

1212
01:29:53,116 --> 01:29:56,786
Come to the courthouse at exactly 10:15
with the printouts.

1213
01:30:01,166 --> 01:30:04,502
Mr. Corliss,
are you incarcerated at this time?

1214
01:30:07,464 --> 01:30:08,965
No, now I'm just in a courtroom.

1215
01:30:11,259 --> 01:30:16,598
But you are currently being held
in the jail ward at USC hospital, correct?

1216
01:30:16,681 --> 01:30:21,937
-Yeah. Since I got arrested.
-For burglary and drug possession?

1217
01:30:22,729 --> 01:30:25,273
-That's right.
-Now,

1218
01:30:27,901 --> 01:30:29,277
do you know the defendant?

1219
01:30:31,196 --> 01:30:36,034
Yeah. I met him in lockup.
We was bused over from jail.

1220
01:30:36,117 --> 01:30:39,204
Then we were together in the tank
when we came for first appearances.

1221
01:30:39,287 --> 01:30:42,082
-Did you talk at that time?
-Yeah.

1222
01:30:42,165 --> 01:30:44,626
Talked about how bad we needed cigarettes.

1223
01:30:44,709 --> 01:30:45,752
Anything else?

1224
01:30:45,835 --> 01:30:49,839
You know, "What are you in for?" Like that.

1225
01:30:50,131 --> 01:30:53,093
And did he say what he was in for?

1226
01:30:53,176 --> 01:30:57,430
He said, "For giving a bitch
exactly what she deserved."

1227
01:30:57,514 --> 01:30:58,765
Those were his words.

1228
01:30:59,683 --> 01:31:03,228
"For giving a bitch
exactly what she deserved."

1229
01:31:04,688 --> 01:31:07,190
Now, have I or anyone else promised you

1230
01:31:07,273 --> 01:31:09,067
anything in exchange
for your testimony today?

1231
01:31:09,150 --> 01:31:14,280
-No. It's just the right thing to do.
-Thank you, Your Honor.

1232
01:31:30,547 --> 01:31:33,883
How many times have you been arrested,
Mr. Corliss?

1233
01:31:35,343 --> 01:31:37,679
About seven times in LA.

1234
01:31:37,762 --> 01:31:40,640
A couple more in Phoenix and New York,
if you want to count those.

1235
01:31:40,724 --> 01:31:43,560
Yeah, so you know
how the system works, yeah?

1236
01:31:43,643 --> 01:31:45,562
- I try to survive.
-Right.

1237
01:31:45,729 --> 01:31:48,106
Does that sometimes mean
ratting out fellow inmates?

1238
01:31:48,189 --> 01:31:49,941
Your Honor, I object.

1239
01:31:50,025 --> 01:31:53,278
Take a seat, Mr. Minton.
I gave you leeway bringing this witness in.

1240
01:31:53,653 --> 01:31:56,281
Thank you, Your Honor, but I'll rephrase.

1241
01:31:56,364 --> 01:32:00,326
What I'm asking you is how many times
have you snitched on a fellow inmate?

1242
01:32:00,410 --> 01:32:02,704
-This makes my fourth.
-This makes your fourth time.

1243
01:32:02,787 --> 01:32:08,043
Four times you've testified
for the prosecution against a fellow inmate.

1244
01:32:08,585 --> 01:32:10,545
It makes you a popular man, Mr. Corliss.

1245
01:32:10,628 --> 01:32:14,007
It sounds like people just come up to you,
tell you the crimes that they've committed,

1246
01:32:14,090 --> 01:32:16,634
SO you can come in here
and testify against them.

1247
01:32:16,718 --> 01:32:18,553
People talk to me. I'm a friendly guy.

1248
01:32:18,636 --> 01:32:22,432
You're a friendly guy? And you're saying
you and my client were friends?

1249
01:32:22,515 --> 01:32:24,017
We was friendly.

1250
01:32:24,100 --> 01:32:27,604
So, he just said to you what you just told us
and told the jury,

1251
01:32:27,687 --> 01:32:30,940
that he gave a woman "what she deserved"?

1252
01:32:31,399 --> 01:32:33,860
And then the two of you
went back to talking about cigarettes?

1253
01:32:33,943 --> 01:32:36,613
Not exactly. It's like he was bragging.

1254
01:32:38,364 --> 01:32:42,577
He told me he did it before.
Said the other time he killed the bitch.

1255
01:32:42,786 --> 01:32:46,081
He got away with it then,
he'd get away with it now.

1256
01:32:49,250 --> 01:32:50,627
Mr. Haller.

1257
01:32:56,299 --> 01:33:00,011
I have no more questions, Your Honor.

1258
01:33:00,095 --> 01:33:01,429
Redirect, Your Honor.

1259
01:33:07,060 --> 01:33:08,061
What the hell is this?

1260
01:33:08,144 --> 01:33:09,354
You tell me.

1261
01:33:09,437 --> 01:33:14,067
-What the hell did you say to this guy, huh?
-Nothing. This is a setup. You're doing this.

1262
01:33:14,150 --> 01:33:17,112
How? How am I doing this?

1263
01:33:20,365 --> 01:33:23,409
You say he was bragging. How?

1264
01:33:23,493 --> 01:33:27,956
Well, like, he told me the details.
Of the other one, that he killed.

1265
01:33:30,291 --> 01:33:33,378
She was a dancer at some club,

1266
01:33:34,129 --> 01:33:38,174
and she had a sexy snake tattoo
wrapped around her body.

1267
01:33:41,845 --> 01:33:45,014
-Did he say anything else?
-No.

1268
01:33:47,976 --> 01:33:50,103
The snake girl stuff was it.

1269
01:33:52,522 --> 01:33:56,151
-How does he know this, Louis?
-Do you think I know?

1270
01:33:56,234 --> 01:34:00,155
No. If you didn't tell him this shit,
somebody did.

1271
01:34:00,238 --> 01:34:02,407
I'd start thinking about who that could be.

1272
01:34:02,490 --> 01:34:04,534
Then I have no further questions,
Your Honor.

1273
01:34:06,327 --> 01:34:08,538
Any recross from the defense?

1274
01:34:13,835 --> 01:34:17,797
-A moment with my staff, Your Honor?
-Be quick.

1275
01:34:17,881 --> 01:34:19,591
-Is it all here?
-Yeah.

1276
01:34:19,674 --> 01:34:22,844
Okay, good. Now listen, you go now.
Leave the building.

1277
01:34:22,927 --> 01:34:23,970
I don't want anyone asking you questions,

1278
01:34:24,053 --> 01:34:25,013
-you got it?
-Okay.

1279
01:34:25,096 --> 01:34:26,097
All right.

1280
01:34:27,640 --> 01:34:33,229
-Dwayne. Mind if I call you that?
-Sure, man. Wow on the assistant.

1281
01:34:35,231 --> 01:34:38,735
You're a funny guy, DJ.

1282
01:34:38,818 --> 01:34:40,195
"DJ."

1283
01:34:40,278 --> 01:34:43,865
Isn't that what they call you, for example,
down in Phoenix?

1284
01:34:44,574 --> 01:34:45,533
Maybe.

1285
01:34:45,617 --> 01:34:48,494
Well, my assistant,
the one whose number you want,

1286
01:34:48,578 --> 01:34:52,957
she was reading on the Internet
about a DJ Corliss,

1287
01:34:53,041 --> 01:34:57,337
arrested in 1989 on drug charges,
hometown of Mesa, Arizona.

1288
01:34:58,087 --> 01:35:00,798
-Yeah, that'd be me.
-You do remember Fred Bentley, right?

1289
01:35:02,425 --> 01:35:05,053
Your Honor,
where is the defense going with this?

1290
01:35:05,136 --> 01:35:09,140
Make a connection soon, Mr. Haller.
But the witness will answer.

1291
01:35:10,099 --> 01:35:12,352
- I don't remember any Bentley.
-Sure you do.

1292
01:35:12,435 --> 01:35:16,981
You testified that he confessed to you
the crime that he was charged with.

1293
01:35:17,065 --> 01:35:21,444
Raping a 10-year-old girl.
But he denied it in court.

1294
01:35:22,779 --> 01:35:24,739
Am I ringing any bells, DJ?

1295
01:35:25,740 --> 01:35:28,618
In 1989, I was high a lot. I don't...
Not much I recall.

1296
01:35:28,701 --> 01:35:31,162
Then I'd like you to read this for us.

1297
01:35:31,246 --> 01:35:35,041
Your Honor, this is a news report
from the Arizona Star, 1997,

1298
01:35:35,124 --> 01:35:39,963
eight years after Mr. Bentley was convicted.
I ask that it be admitted into evidence.

1299
01:35:41,464 --> 01:35:44,717
Your Honor, a news report?

1300
01:35:45,718 --> 01:35:48,721
Let's see where it takes us.
The state can object later.

1301
01:35:49,430 --> 01:35:51,975
Thank you, Your Honor.

1302
01:35:52,141 --> 01:35:54,686
If you could read this for us, Mr. Corliss.

1303
01:35:54,769 --> 01:35:57,355
I've highlighted the part
I'd like for you to read.

1304
01:35:57,438 --> 01:36:00,024
-I'm not good at reading.
-That's okay. You can take your time.

1305
01:36:00,108 --> 01:36:02,110
We'll make it through it.

1306
01:36:04,028 --> 01:36:07,240
"A man, Frederick Bentley,

1307
01:36:09,117 --> 01:36:12,412
"wrongly convicted of rape,
was released Saturday

1308
01:36:12,495 --> 01:36:16,291
"after conclusive DNA results
cleared him of the crime.

1309
01:36:16,374 --> 01:36:21,587
"The case was bolstered at trial
by testimony from an informant,

1310
01:36:21,671 --> 01:36:25,300
"DJ Corliss of Mesa,
who claimed Bentley had bragged to him

1311
01:36:25,383 --> 01:36:27,302
"about the rape
while together in the holding cell."

1312
01:36:27,385 --> 01:36:30,346
That's enough. Thank you, Mr. Corliss.

1313
01:36:31,681 --> 01:36:34,767
Were you charged with perjury
in this incident, DJ?

1314
01:36:34,851 --> 01:36:36,185
No, I was not.

1315
01:36:36,311 --> 01:36:39,439
Is that because the prosecution
was complicit in your confession?

1316
01:36:39,522 --> 01:36:40,565
Judge!

1317
01:36:40,732 --> 01:36:43,443
Were you promised the same thing here,
Mr. Corliss,

1318
01:36:43,526 --> 01:36:46,279
to say that Louis Roulet bragged to you
in the holding cell?

1319
01:36:46,362 --> 01:36:48,865
Isn't that what happened?
You lied then and you're lying now!

1320
01:36:48,948 --> 01:36:52,660
-All right, Mr. Haller! That will do!
-Objection, Your Honor!

1321
01:36:52,744 --> 01:36:55,705
I'm sorry, Your Honor.
I have no more questions.

1322
01:36:56,748 --> 01:37:00,752
I'm excusing the jury for an early lunch.
Bailiff, see them out.

1323
01:37:07,717 --> 01:37:10,678
Mr. Minton,
do you know what you have done?

1324
01:37:11,554 --> 01:37:14,807
You've put a documented liar on the stand,

1325
01:37:14,891 --> 01:37:18,061
a man with a record
of putting innocent people in prison...

1326
01:37:18,186 --> 01:37:20,396
-Your Honor.
-Shut the hell up when I'm talking to you!

1327
01:37:24,192 --> 01:37:27,528
I can think of nothing
more prejudicial or corrupt

1328
01:37:28,071 --> 01:37:30,948
than what I just saw out there.

1329
01:37:31,115 --> 01:37:33,743
Do you realize what you've done to my trial?

1330
01:37:51,302 --> 01:37:54,055
He's going to talk to his boss
to decide what they want to do

1331
01:37:54,138 --> 01:37:56,808
before the judge comes down
with a directed verdict.

1332
01:37:56,891 --> 01:37:58,684
What's a directed verdict?

1333
01:37:58,768 --> 01:38:02,897
It's where the judge takes the case
from the jury's hands, declares an acquittal.

1334
01:38:02,980 --> 01:38:04,357
Oh, my God.

1335
01:38:06,109 --> 01:38:08,486
We'll know more in a few minutes.

1336
01:38:16,077 --> 01:38:20,373
I want to know
how Corliss got that shit he's saying!

1337
01:38:20,456 --> 01:38:23,209
Maybe Frank Levin told him.

1338
01:38:23,292 --> 01:38:28,464
Maybe he found something and gave it
to Corliss, and that's why you killed him.

1339
01:38:45,857 --> 01:38:47,817
Court's back in session.

1340
01:38:51,487 --> 01:38:54,031
Your Honor,
I spoke with the district attorney.

1341
01:38:54,115 --> 01:38:58,244
The state wishes to dismiss all charges.
You have the motion in front of you.

1342
01:38:58,327 --> 01:39:00,329
This is a motion to dismiss with prejudice.

1343
01:39:00,872 --> 01:39:03,332
-Case closed.
-Yes, Your Honor.

1344
01:39:03,416 --> 01:39:06,919
Mr. Roulet, you're free to go.
Court's adjourned.

1345
01:39:09,505 --> 01:39:13,926
-Mr. Haller, thank you so much for my son.
-You're welcome.

1346
01:39:14,010 --> 01:39:16,304
-You were splendid.
-Thank you.

1347
01:39:21,350 --> 01:39:24,604
-I want the gun.
-Of course you do.

1348
01:39:26,314 --> 01:39:27,315
I want to talk.

1349
01:39:27,857 --> 01:39:28,858
Mr. Haller,

1350
01:39:29,484 --> 01:39:32,862
I insist you join us for dinner tonight
for a celebration.

1351
01:39:32,945 --> 01:39:35,781
-I don't think so.
-Louis Roulet,

1352
01:39:35,865 --> 01:39:38,618
-you're under arrest.
-What do you think you're doing?

1353
01:39:38,701 --> 01:39:40,453
-Be quiet, Mother.
-Hands behind your back!

1354
01:39:40,536 --> 01:39:41,537
What's the charge?

1355
01:39:41,621 --> 01:39:44,624
He's under arrest
for the murder of Donna Renteria.

1356
01:39:44,707 --> 01:39:48,294
-Everything that man said was a lie!
-You have the right to remain silent.

1357
01:39:48,377 --> 01:39:50,796
You have the right to have
an attorney present during questioning.

1358
01:39:50,880 --> 01:39:52,965
If you give up that right, anything you say

1359
01:39:53,049 --> 01:39:55,134
can and will be used against you
in a court of law.

1360
01:39:55,218 --> 01:39:57,220
Do you understand your rights
as I've read them to you?

1361
01:39:57,720 --> 01:40:01,015
Hey! Look at me!
Do you understand your rights?

1362
01:40:01,098 --> 01:40:03,726
Detective, can I have a word with him?

1363
01:40:08,397 --> 01:40:12,109
Well, that's it, Louis. I got you off.

1364
01:40:13,069 --> 01:40:16,697
Time to find yourself a new lawyer.

1365
01:40:16,781 --> 01:40:19,408
I've still got your gun.

1366
01:40:20,743 --> 01:40:23,871
And you're gonna have to explain
how you got it.

1367
01:40:28,793 --> 01:40:31,504
-Thank you, Detective.
-Come on, Louis.

1368
01:40:39,303 --> 01:40:42,557
-Mary...
-Not a word. You get my kid out of jail.

1369
01:40:42,640 --> 01:40:45,935
Haller, you are one
messed-up son of a bitch.

1370
01:40:46,435 --> 01:40:51,524
First you get your client off for assault,
only to burn him for murder.

1371
01:40:52,608 --> 01:40:56,696
You don't have enough to charge him
with the Renteria murder, do you?

1372
01:40:56,779 --> 01:40:58,447
They've got enough to screw with him.

1373
01:40:58,948 --> 01:41:01,826
There's no way the DA
was letting Roulet walk out of here,

1374
01:41:01,909 --> 01:41:04,120
not after what just happened.

1375
01:41:06,163 --> 01:41:10,126
I don't get you, Haller.
Whose side are you on, anyway?

1376
01:41:28,144 --> 01:41:29,562
God damn it!

1377
01:41:32,898 --> 01:41:33,983
Earl!

1378
01:41:36,819 --> 01:41:37,820
Dude.

1379
01:41:38,779 --> 01:41:41,741
Hey, I'm sorry, boss. Look, I stepped away
for half a minute, all right?

1380
01:41:41,824 --> 01:41:44,702
-All right. All right, all right.
-You can take the ticket out of my pay.

1381
01:41:44,785 --> 01:41:47,288
You don't make enough. This one's on me.
Let's roll.

1382
01:41:47,371 --> 01:41:48,372
All right.

1383
01:41:50,458 --> 01:41:53,669
All right, let's go to the house, Earl.

1384
01:41:54,712 --> 01:41:57,965
Hey, boss.
You know that favor you asked me?

1385
01:42:02,345 --> 01:42:05,848
A guy I know, he picked it up on the street.
Real clean.

1386
01:42:58,275 --> 01:43:01,362
-Hey, boss, be careful, all right?
-Yes, Sir.

1387
01:43:31,475 --> 01:43:34,895
Mick, it's me. I tried you on your cell.
Sorry to interrupt your day with Hayley,

1388
01:43:34,979 --> 01:43:37,064
but you asked me to dig on Roulet.

1389
01:43:37,148 --> 01:43:40,651
Remember? You said you didn't buy it
that all he had was parking tickets?

1390
01:43:40,735 --> 01:43:43,320
Well, I might have found...

1391
01:43:43,529 --> 01:43:45,030
Maggie, I got it.

1392
01:43:45,114 --> 01:43:47,074
- I think I know why Frank Levin got killed.
-Yeah?

1393
01:43:47,158 --> 01:43:49,577
All right, call Lankford.
Have him pull up Roulet's driving record,

1394
01:43:49,660 --> 01:43:51,162
every ticket he ever got.

1395
01:43:51,245 --> 01:43:54,707
That's what Frank did. He said
he found Martinez's ticket out of the Q.

1396
01:43:54,790 --> 01:43:55,958
I just never knew what he meant.

1397
01:43:56,041 --> 01:43:57,710
Okay, done,
but I have to tell you something.

1398
01:43:57,877 --> 01:44:01,922
They let Roulet go. They didn't have
enough to hold him. You were right.

1399
01:44:02,006 --> 01:44:03,507
I guess the family got involved.

1400
01:44:03,591 --> 01:44:06,218
-Maggie, is Hayley with you?
-She's at my sister's. Why?

1401
01:44:06,302 --> 01:44:09,889
Go to your sister's, stay with Hayley,
and wait for my call. You got it?

1402
01:44:09,972 --> 01:44:11,348
Okay.

1403
01:44:16,395 --> 01:44:19,148
-Val, it's Mick Haller.
-Hey, Mick, haven't heard from you

1404
01:44:19,231 --> 01:44:22,860
since you busted into my office and accused
me of conspiracy to commit murder, huh?

1405
01:44:22,943 --> 01:44:25,196
If I had any self-respect,
I'd hang up on you right now.

1406
01:44:25,488 --> 01:44:27,531
It was Frank dying, all right?
I was out of my head.

1407
01:44:27,615 --> 01:44:30,117
- Need you to do me a favor.
-You need a favor? Okay.

1408
01:44:30,201 --> 01:44:33,579
You got more balls than a Chinese
ping-pong tournament. I'll give you that.

1409
01:44:33,662 --> 01:44:36,791
Listen, man, you can kick my ass later,
all right? It's important.

1410
01:44:36,874 --> 01:44:39,710
-Is Roulet still wearing the tracer?
-Yeah, yeah, he is, yeah.

1411
01:44:39,794 --> 01:44:43,172
I got a call. He's coming in the morning
to get it off. I guess they kicked him, huh?

1412
01:44:43,380 --> 01:44:46,300
-Yeah. I need you to track him for me.
-Man, I can't.

1413
01:44:46,675 --> 01:44:48,677
I can't.
I got a little biddy coming in a few minutes.

1414
01:44:48,803 --> 01:44:50,262
Val, Val! Stop whatever you're doing.

1415
01:44:50,346 --> 01:44:54,183
I need it, man. I need you to do it now.
It's about my family.

1416
01:44:58,187 --> 01:44:59,188
Yeah?

1417
01:44:59,855 --> 01:45:02,858
It's me.
He's headed up north on San Fernando.

1418
01:45:03,359 --> 01:45:06,445
Mick, I think he's headed for your house.
Do you want me to call the cops for you?

1419
01:45:06,529 --> 01:45:07,530
Bullshit.

1420
01:45:07,863 --> 01:45:10,866
I'm telling you,
he just passed Dodger Stadium.

1421
01:45:10,950 --> 01:45:13,619
No, no, no, he's not going to my house, Val.

1422
01:45:15,120 --> 01:45:16,247
You're right, you're right, Mick.

1423
01:45:16,330 --> 01:45:18,749
He just shot past your street.
He's not headed for your house.

1424
01:45:19,208 --> 01:45:21,210
I know where he's going.

1425
01:45:23,087 --> 01:45:27,049
Hello? You're welcome. No, it's all right.
Don't worry about it.

1426
01:46:13,053 --> 01:46:16,599
Hello, Louis. My family's here.

1427
01:46:17,892 --> 01:46:20,102
- I know.
-You bring your knife?

1428
01:46:21,228 --> 01:46:22,479
And my gun?

1429
01:46:23,814 --> 01:46:26,191
-Maybe.
-Good.

1430
01:46:30,279 --> 01:46:33,699
"Cause I brought this.

1431
01:46:33,782 --> 01:46:37,036
You got one chance
to turn around and leave.

1432
01:46:39,955 --> 01:46:41,457
And then what?

1433
01:46:43,459 --> 01:46:47,421
You gonna keep coming back every night?
Every day?

1434
01:46:49,965 --> 01:46:54,011
Or just try to get me sent up to San Quentin
like Jesus Martinez?

1435
01:46:54,303 --> 01:46:56,388
No.

1436
01:46:56,472 --> 01:47:00,559
I'm not quitting until Martinez is free
and you're convicted of murder.

1437
01:47:00,935 --> 01:47:03,771
And when that needle goes in your arm,

1438
01:47:06,315 --> 01:47:08,525
that will be me.

1439
01:47:10,319 --> 01:47:12,529
Well, why don't you
just shoot me right now?

1440
01:47:15,366 --> 01:47:17,868
I don't think I'll have to.

1441
01:47:19,161 --> 01:47:20,245
Hey!

1442
01:47:22,998 --> 01:47:25,334
That's my car! What are you doing?

1443
01:47:31,465 --> 01:47:33,842
Come on, now, get him up. Get up!

1444
01:47:35,844 --> 01:47:37,346
Hospital, not the morgue.

1445
01:48:01,870 --> 01:48:05,165
-Hey, Mags.
-You were right, Mick. Roulet got a ticket

1446
01:48:05,249 --> 01:48:08,961
outside of Renteria's apartment
on the night that she was murdered.

1447
01:48:09,044 --> 01:48:11,171
It's all gonna be on the DA's desk
in the morning.

1448
01:48:11,880 --> 01:48:14,800
-Where are you?
-Just about home.

1449
01:48:14,883 --> 01:48:17,469
What do you say I come pick up
you and Hayley at your sister's place

1450
01:48:17,553 --> 01:48:19,805
in an hour
and we go out for a nice dinner, huh?

1451
01:48:19,888 --> 01:48:23,183
Great. Yeah. See you in an hour.

1452
01:48:44,288 --> 01:48:47,249
Breaking and entering, huh?

1453
01:48:47,916 --> 01:48:50,794
Just like your son.

1454
01:48:50,878 --> 01:48:52,588
You knew, Mr. Haller.

1455
01:48:52,671 --> 01:48:54,840
You need to get the hell out of my house,
Mrs. Windsor.

1456
01:48:55,215 --> 01:48:56,884
You knew. You set him up.

1457
01:48:56,967 --> 01:49:01,138
The only person who was set up here
was me.

1458
01:49:01,221 --> 01:49:04,600
-And how'd that turn out for you?
-You have no idea who we are.

1459
01:49:04,725 --> 01:49:08,187
I know that your son Louis is going down
for the murder of Donna Renteria.

1460
01:49:08,645 --> 01:49:11,857
I also know that I'm gonna burn his ass
for killing my friend, Frank Levin.

1461
01:49:11,940 --> 01:49:13,609
-He didn't kill him.
-Yes, he did.

1462
01:49:13,859 --> 01:49:17,863
He beat the tracer and he killed him.
Look, I'm not gonna talk about it with you.

1463
01:49:17,946 --> 01:49:20,574
Now, for the last time,
get the hell out of my house.

1464
01:49:20,657 --> 01:49:24,203
-You're not listening to me.
-No, you're not listening to me.

1465
01:49:24,286 --> 01:49:26,622
Mrs. Windsor, get the hell out of my house.

1466
01:49:27,956 --> 01:49:30,793
I told you my son didn't kill Frank Levin.

1467
01:49:32,127 --> 01:49:33,128
I did.

1468
01:49:58,195 --> 01:50:00,030
911, what's your emergency?

1469
01:50:28,684 --> 01:50:31,436
I thought I told you to be careful, man.

1470
01:50:33,355 --> 01:50:38,026
-Yeah, that's enough.
-Nobody till somebody shoots you.

1471
01:50:43,073 --> 01:50:47,369
-Hey, boss, feeling all right?
-Yeah, Earl. Solid.

1472
01:50:48,537 --> 01:50:51,540
Yeah, I heard down at the courthouse
that Martinez is out. Is that right?

1473
01:50:52,875 --> 01:50:54,960
Yeah, it is.

1474
01:50:55,043 --> 01:50:59,423
And Roulet,
they're going for the death penalty on him?

1475
01:50:59,506 --> 01:51:01,133
Martinez is free.

1476
01:51:12,352 --> 01:51:16,023
-Boss, we got company.
-Yeah, I see that.

1477
01:51:16,106 --> 01:51:18,901
Pull over up here to the left, say hello.

1478
01:51:48,388 --> 01:51:50,390
What do you say, Eddie?

1479
01:51:50,474 --> 01:51:53,810
-You took one for the team, huh?
-Yeah.

1480
01:51:53,894 --> 01:51:58,273
-Did you really shoot your client's mother?
-Damn right I did. She shot me first.

1481
01:52:00,943 --> 01:52:03,278
Well, I'm glad you're better,

1482
01:52:03,779 --> 01:52:07,699
'cause my boy Harold, old hard case...

1483
01:52:07,783 --> 01:52:08,951
Don't tell me.

1484
01:52:09,034 --> 01:52:12,871
Yeah, he got caught with 50 kilos
in his girlfriend's minivan.

1485
01:52:13,330 --> 01:52:15,457
The girlfriend's some cop's wife.

1486
01:52:15,540 --> 01:52:17,876
-That doesn't help.
-No.

1487
01:52:17,960 --> 01:52:20,921
You're the only help he's got, Counselor.

1488
01:52:22,464 --> 01:52:24,841
All right. Call me with the details.

1489
01:52:24,925 --> 01:52:27,386
I gotta say, though,
the way things went down,

1490
01:52:27,469 --> 01:52:32,349
I think we earned a little discount.
Say, half your fee.

1491
01:52:37,062 --> 01:52:40,232
I tell you what, Eddie.

1492
01:52:40,315 --> 01:52:42,651
How about I do this one for free?

1493
01:52:49,866 --> 01:52:54,746
-Are you sure you're feeling all right?
-Repeat customers, Earl.

1494
01:52:54,830 --> 01:52:56,581
We'll stick it to them next time.

